		<Item class="ModuleScript" referent="RBX6A443C8E470642D1968FC3305A4977D0">
			<Properties>
				<Content name="LinkedSource"><null></null></Content>
				<ProtectedString name="Source"><![CDATA[return {
  {
    v = "1.4.5",
    notes = [[
    This is the first part of a bigger update. The next one will fix some known bugs and add new API methods.

    ## New features
    - Added color picker and color swapper

    ## Fixes
    - Camera shake preset now appears in VFX Adder
    - Added missing falloff attribute to camera shakes
    - Removed a duplicate input bar for the font setting
    - Fixed beziers not cleaning up when duration is 0
    - Object cache now correctly disposes of excess objects
    ]],
  },
  {
    v = "1.4.0",
    notes = [[
    ## New features
    - Added camera shakes
    - Added optional _START_VALUE for tween properties

    ## Fixes
    - Fixed a bug with path particle visualization
    - Fixed tween properties getting the start value before delay
    - Fixed bezier projectiles
    ]],
  },
  {
    v = "1.3.5",
    notes = [[
    ## New features
    - Added studio-level keybinds
    - Added Start and End offset for rings and lines

    ## Changes
    - Mesh and bezier speed is now applied globally when EmitDuration is non-zero

    ## Fixes
    - Improved keybind behavior in curve editor
    - Fixed Copier not copying mesh decal Color3 property
    ]],
  },
  {
    v = "1.3.0",
    notes = [[
    ## New features
    - Added Start and End Size curves for Shockwave Lines & Rings
    - Added Offset for Shockwave Lines & Rings
    - Added Airtime for Shockwave Debris
    - Added keybinds for emitting, toggling enabled effects, and toggling paths
    - Added settings for different button layouts

    ## Changes
    - Added SpecialMeshes to the Start and End parts of the 'Part Mesh' and 'Decal Mesh' presets

    ## Fixes
    - Fixed Shockwave Debris Min & Max direction not being converted to world space correctly
    - Shared part cache now also cleans up the linear and angular velocities of freed parts
    - Mesh decals now show up in the Attributes window when a mesh is selected
    ]],
  },
  {
    v = "1.2.0",
    notes = [[
    ## New features
    - Added 'FixedAmount' for Shockwave Lines

    ## Improvements
    ### Shockwave Line precision
        + Lines now create the exact amount of rocks calculated from current rate and duration, instead of approximately matching this value with a wide margin of error

        + Lines now create rocks precisely where they are supposed to be by not relying on the current elapsed time

        + Lines can now create more than 1 rock on each frame if needed (this is a very good improvement for very short durations)

    ### Performance
        + All rock effects now use the shared part cache, improving performance considerably (the reference part is still cloned when it has any effects to be emitted)

    ### ObjectCache
        + Object cache now detects when a cached object is destroyed and removes it from the cache

        + The empty space created by destroyed objects is refilled by new non-excess parts created on each recycle interval

    ## Changes
    - Increased the minimum amount of parts in the shared part cache from 50 to 150 in order to accommodate rock effects

    - Increased the recycle interval from 10 seconds to 15 seconds

    ## Fixes
    - Fixed a dumb version checker bug
    - Fixed a separator appearing on top of containers in the Attributes window
    ]],
  },
  {
    v = "1.1.2",
    notes = [[
    ## Fixes
    - Fixed Copier copying from the first ever selected effect instead of using currently selected effect
    ]],
  },
  {
    v = "1.1.1",
    notes = [[
      ## New features
      - Added EmitCount to meshes
      - Added SpreadAngle to meshes
      - Added RotAroundOrigin to make random rotation rotate around the origin (start) of the mesh
      - VFX in the mesh 'Start' part are now emitted (with EmitOnFinish support)

      ## Fixes
      - Fixed insane lag when there are a lot of unanchored parts in workspace (this was probably a roblox bug)
      - Fixed Curve Editor point properties dividing by 0 when start and end values are 0, and when time is 0

      ## Removed features
      - Removed mesh Start part rotation sync (in favor of the new rotation attributes)
    ]],
  },
  {
    v = "1.1.0",
    notes = [[
      ## New features
      - Added Tween Properties
      - Added random rotation for beziers and meshes
      - Added speed curve for beziers

      ## Changes
      - Curve copier now copies and pastes curve attributes
      - Curve copier now allows copying and pasting from Speed to TimeScale and vice-versa

      ## Other important things
      - Added support for NumberRange curve inputs
      - Added an error message when CreateAssetAsync API is unavailable
      - Point properties now correctly set Value and LeftTangent
      - Fixed several UI bugs with non-standard scaling

      ## Misc
      - Fixed search in flipbook importer
      - Removed minimization for attribute containers in the Attributes window
    ]],
  },
  {
    v = "1.0.0",
    notes = [[
      # Release
      The plugin has been finally released after being almost 4 months in development!

      There are still many things I want to add, but it's finally in a usable state.

      The plugin has a lot of features, so I recommend checking out the documentation, which is currently in an unfinished state, but has all of the effects roughly documented.

      We also have a barebones Discord server, so feel free to join if you have any questions.

      Many thanks go to Kinnie for helping me test and direct the plugin to where it is now.
    ]],
  },
}
]]></ProtectedString>
